# TU ECE report template (canonical reference)

When editing WheelSense thesis LaTeX under [`Thesis/latex/`](Thesis/latex/), **treat the pinned upstream template as the structural and style reference**:

- **Path:** [`Thesis/Example/reporttemplate-0.0.1/`](Thesis/Example/reporttemplate-0.0.1/) — tag **v0.0.1** from [tueceproj/reporttemplate](https://github.com/tueceproj/reporttemplate).

## What to align from the template

- **Entry document:** compare [`Thesis/latex/thesis.tex`](Thesis/latex/thesis.tex) with `latex/thesis.tex` in the template (front matter order, `\mainmatter`, back matter).
- **Style packages:** `TUthesis.sty`, `mystyle.sty` — behaviour and package set should stay compatible with the template unless the faculty explicitly requires a project-specific deviation (document that deviation in a short comment near the change).
- **Front matter naming and list order:** follow faculty examples (abstracts, acknowledgements, LoT/LoF order, symbols list titles) — use the template’s `front/` and `latex/` files as the baseline when in doubt.
- **Do not** copy sample chapter body text from the template into the real thesis; only structure, macros, and formatting patterns.

## Project vs template paths

- Live thesis sources live under **`Thesis/latex/`** (not the template’s flat `chapter1.tex` layout). Map template concepts to `Thesis/latex/content/chapters/`, `Thesis/latex/front/`, `Thesis/latex/meta/info.tex`.

## Updating the pin

To refresh the reference tree (e.g. new faculty tag), replace `Thesis/Example/reporttemplate-0.0.1/` with the new checkout and note the tag in this rule or in `Thesis/README.md` if present.
